Syntax-wise I&#39;d suggest the following:

    function List = findVLInd(FL, StartingPoint)
    
      List = StartingPoint;
    
      for a = 1:50000
        List(end+1, :) = [find(List(a,1)==FL(:,1))];
                          find(List(a,1)==FL(:,2))];
                          find(List(a,1)==FL(:,3))];
    
        Lz = FL(List,:);
        List(end+1:end+size(Lz,1), :) = [Lz(:,1);Lz(:,2);Lz(:,3)];
        List = unique(List);
      end 
    end


This removes the reassignment operation `List = [List; X]` which copies the content of list into another variable then deletes it (though the new variable has the same name as the previous one) and replaces it with an appending operation, which is much faster in Matlab, though still slow. By calling the first three lines in your `for` loop in a single block, I can also reduce the number of such operations.

As per the comments by [ChrisLuengo](https://stackoverflow.com/users/7328782/cris-luengo) and [pacta-sunt-servanda](https://stackoverflow.com/users/3684758/pacta-sunt-servanda), there are other issues you might want to address that aim at improving the functionality of your code.

